      "id": "4b37e5c4",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4b37e5c4"
      },
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "# MacroAnchor CurveRV V2 — Sparse greedy curve allocation + residualized RV tests\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook tests two extensions in parallel, using the same MacroAnchor signal stack as V1.\n",
        "\n",
        "The goal is deliberately narrow:\n",
        "\n",
        "> Does the macro-anchored term-premium surface support a **systematic curve portfolio** beyond the documented 10Y duration-risk-premium result?\n",
        "\n",
        "V1 showed that a naive top/bottom tenor spread is too crude. V2 therefore tests two more disciplined branches.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Track A — Sparse greedy curve allocator\n",
        "\n",
        "This branch adapts the logic of a greedy sparse SAA allocator to the yield curve.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Core leg:** the tenor with the highest expected excess return, selected by **pure return**, not risk-adjusted return.\n",
        "- **Satellite/hedge legs:** additional tenors are accepted only if they improve the portfolio objective under conditional risk.\n",
        "- Conditional risk is tested in two versions:\n",
        "  - return-volatility risk: \\(\\sqrt{w'\\Sigma_{rx,t}w}\\);\n",
        "  - rates-native DV01/yield-shock risk: \\(\\sqrt{(D w)'\\Sigma_{\\Delta y,t}(D w)}\\).\n",
        "\n",
        "Implemented variants:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. `G1_sparse_core_vol`: long-only sparse allocator using conditional return volatility.\n",
        "2. `G2_sparse_core_dv01`: long-only sparse allocator using conditional DV01/yield-shock risk.\n",
        "3. `G3_core_short_dv01`: core best-tenor plus short hedge legs, accepted only if they improve risk-adjusted profile.\n",
        "4. `G4_core_tail_es`: core best-tenor allocator using rolling historical ES as risk proxy.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Track B — Residualized/carry-aware curve RV\n",
        "\n",
        "This branch tests the stricter RV hypothesis: after removing common tenor-level effects, do residual term-premium deviations contain tradable curve information?\n",
        "\n",
        "Implemented variants:\n",
        "\n",
        "5. `R1_resid_top2_bottom2`: long top-2 / short bottom-2 residualized TP tenors.\n",
        "6. `R2_resid_carry_dv01`: residualized TP plus carry/roll score, DV01-neutral.\n",
        "7. `R3_resid_carry_dv01_smooth`: same as R2 with turnover smoothing.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Reading rule\n",
        "\n",
        "- If `G1/G2/G3/G4` work but `R1/R2/R3` do not: the signal is best framed as **sparse duration / tenor allocation**, not pure curve RV.\n",
        "- If `R2/R3` work after costs with low beta to 10Y: the project upgrades toward **macro-anchored yield-curve relative value**.\n",
        "- If none of the V2 branches work: the paper remains stronger as a 10Y bond-risk-premium / specification-audit paper, with the curve strategies reported as honest extensions.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
